--- body ---
## Context

Discovery 2026-04-30: Claude Code's `~/.claude/scripts/on-start.sh` was
appending all `~/.claude/.env` keys into `$CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`. Claude Code
inlines that file's contents as `KEY=value` prefix in every spawned
`bash -c` command line — making secrets visible to anyone running
`ps -ef` on the host (and to auditd / container telemetry / shared-host
neighbours). An accidental `ps -ef` during AEDIST work leaked the entire
key set into a chat transcript; the keys had to be rotated.

User-side fix (committed in `~/.claude/scripts/on-start.sh`): the hook
no longer persists `.env` into `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`. Tools that need keys
must source `.env` explicitly.

## Project-specific work

This repo uses uv (`pyproject.toml` + `uv.lock`) but the top-level
`Makefile` has no `uv run` invocations today — uv may be invoked from
shell scripts, dvc stages, quarto pre-render hooks, or CI. **Audit
needed before code changes.**

1. Locate every uv invocation in the repo:
   - `grep -rn "uv run" .`
   - Check `dvc.yaml` stages, `_quarto.yml` pre/post hooks, any shell
     scripts under `scripts/`, `.github/workflows/`.
2. For each invocation that needs an API key (OpenRouter, Anthropic,
   etc.), wrap with `uv run --env-file <path>/.env ...` so uv loads the
   project `.env` at child-process spawn time.
3. Drop any `export KEY := $(shell grep ...)` patterns from Makefiles —
   those put values onto Make's command line and on into spawned process
   args, the same leak path we just closed.
4. Document the chosen env source in a Makefile / dvc.yaml header
   comment. Recommended: project `.env` for project-specific keys;
   `~/.claude/.env` stays only for cross-project personal accounts
   (Anthropic API outside this project, Zotero, etc.).

## Reference

AEDIST `experiments/Makefile` (commit `4000c21`) shows the model
pattern: a single `UV_RUN := uv run --project .. --env-file ../.env`
macro, with a header block documenting the env policy.

## Test

After refactor, sanity check with:
```bash
ps -ef | grep '<some running uv child>' | grep -E '[A-Z_]+=[^[:space:]]+'
```
No `KEY=value` pairs should appear in the command-line column.

## Exit criteria

- All uv invocations use `--env-file` (or the project's wrapper macro).
- No `export KEY := $(shell ...)` patterns referencing secrets in any
  Makefile, dvc.yaml, or build script.
- Project .env declared as canonical source in a header comment.
- One spot-check confirms no leakage via `ps -ef`.
